Business Brief -- Amax Inc.:
   Loss Posted for 4th Period;
   Lower Metals Prices Cited
For the year, net income dropped almost 87% to $30.2
million, or 34 cents a share, from $225.9 million, or $2.58 a
share. Sales were flat at $3.77 billion.
   The company said markets weakened for its metals because
of recession in the U.S. and Europe. It noted that the
decline in demand included Germany as well as Japan, whose
economies it said had remained stronger longer than many
others. Aluminum shipments by Russia and Eastern European
nations also depressed prices in the fourth quarter, it said.